The paper deals with personalized recommendations and re-ranking methods, which are commonly studied in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The use of labeled datasets to incorporate fairness in the recommendations suggests a focus on algorithmic fairness, which is studied in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category. The paper also uses quantitative analysis and machine learning techniques, which are common in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The dataset used in the experiment is a stock photo dataset, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper proposes a method that can be used as a post-processing step for recommender systems, which suggests a focus on Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
